radiographic_examinations.procedure_name: CT ABD & PELVIS W & W/O CONTRAST, ADDL SECTIONS
radiographic_examinations.findings: Mild hepatic steatosis; the appendix is markedly enlarged, measuring up to 15 millimeters in diameter with a small focus of air distally within the appendiceal tip; fluid-filled remainder of the appendix with multiple proximal appendicoliths measuring up to 7 millimeters; mild fatty infiltration within the cecal wall; no free air, no free fluid, no renal or ureteral calculi, no acute fracture, no bony lesions concerning for malignancy or infection.
